variables.name: ✦/_text/text-default
variables.description: Our default text color for most titles, tabs, and body text.

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-secondary
variables.description: Our secondary text color for inactive tabs, labels, timestamps, and other text that needs to be “lighter” in order to create hierarchy.

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-tertiary
variables.description: Primarily used for placeholder text (for example in a search input), or for hierarchy below secondary text. Note that text at this level is below our color contrast threshold, and may not be readable to all users.

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-onbrand
variables.description: Used for text against a “background with a fill color” (for example, a blue / purple background in our “Share” button)

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-brand
variables.description: Text that is tinted to match the current product, typically used for things like links. For specifically referring to concepts in design, we can use color-text-design instead.

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-assistive
variables.description: Pink text used when Figma is assisting you in some way (ex: in auto layout)

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-danger
variables.description: Red text used to alert users about an error.

variables.name: ✦/_text/text-warning
variables.description: Yellow text used to warn users about a potential problem.

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-default
variables.description: Our default icon color

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-secondary
variables.description: Our secondary icon color for inactive elements that need to be “lighter” in order to create hierarchy.

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-tertiary
variables.description: Our tertiary icon color primarily used for carets

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-onbrand
variables.description: Icons against a “background with a fill color” (for example, a blue / purple background in our “Share” button)

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-brand
variables.description: An icon tinted to match the accent color of the current product.

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-assistive
variables.description: Pink icons used when Figma is assisting you in some way.

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-danger
variables.description: Red icons used to alert users about an error.

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-warning
variables.description: Yellow icons used to warn users about a potential problem.

variables.name: ✦/_icon/icon-success
variables.description: Green icons used for confirmation, and approval.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-default
variables.description: Our default background color

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-secondary
variables.description: Our secondary background color for most containers.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-hover
variables.description: A light grey hover fill color behind icons, and selectable elements.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-selected
variables.description: A lightly tinted selected fill color for selected elements.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-menu
variables.description: The dark fill color of our menus

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-toolbar
variables.description: The dark fill color of our UI2 editor toolbar

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-brand
variables.description: A fill tinted to match the accent color of the current product.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-figjam
variables.description: Purple fill color used for backgrounds like a button that opens in FigJam.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-danger
variables.description: Red fill color behind destructive buttons, and error banners.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-warning
variables.description: Yellow fill color for warning banners

variables.name: ✦/_border/border-default
variables.description: Our default border color used as a divider between sections, or around inputs.

variables.name: ✦/_border/border-strong
variables.description: A much darker border color that we can use for emphasis around some UI elements.

variables.name: ✦/_border/border-onbrand-strong
variables.description: Used for borders against a bg-brand background

variables.name: ✦/_border/border-selected
variables.description: Default selection border color we use for focused / selected inputs.

variables.name: ✦/_border/border-selected-strong
variables.description: When presenting a selected border against an already selected background, we sometimes need to increase the prominence of the selected border.

variables.name: ✦/_border/border-menu
variables.description: Used for borders or dividers within a menu element.

variables.name: ✦/_bg/bg-handoff
variables.description: Green fill color used for backgrounds like a button that opens in Dev Mode.
